titles.title: Designating majority membership on certain standing committees of the House.

vote.text: On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to without objection.

action.text: Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

bill.summary: 2/18/1993--Introduced. Elects Representatives Alan Wheat, Jim McDermott, Eleanor Holmes Norton, Sander M. Levin, John Lewis, and William J. Jefferson to the House Committees on the District of Columbia and Representatives John M. Spratt, Jr., to rank following Edolphus Towns, to Government Operations.
